main event: A ground-radar observation of a greenish-blue flame object, changing to white, the size of a volleyball, which was likely a meteor.
interesting points: The object was observed for 10 seconds.
The object's color, trajectory, duration, and apparent speed all pointed to it being a meteor.
The observation was made 2 miles northwest of Collins, Missouri.
The observers included a Major and a Pilot in the USAF Reserve.
The Air Force Technical Intelligence Center requested a preliminary investigation to comply with Air Force regulations.
sighted object: A greenish-blue flame object, changing to white, the size of a volleyball
photographs: No photographs present in the report
